+export const setupToolResponse = () =>
+	`<explicit_instructions type="setup">
+# Resonance Setup
+This skill sets up the Resonance Persistent Memory System when it does not yet exist.
+
+## When to use
+- When \`.resonance/01_state.md\` does not exist
+- When the user explicitly invokes \`/setup\`
+- On the very first chat in a new workspace
+
+## Steps
+
+### Step 1: Welcome
+Greet the user warmly:
+"Welcome to Resonance! 👋
+I'm your personal assistant for everything you want to organize — whether it's work projects, everyday tasks, or creative endeavors.
+To help me remember what we're working on across chat sessions, I'll quickly set up my memory system. This will only take a minute."
+
+### Step 2: Understand the user's goal
+Ask the user what they want to organize:
+<ask_followup_question>
+<question>What would you like to organize with Resonance?</question>
+<options>["💼 Work Project — e.g., product launch, client project, strategy", "🏠 Personal Project — e.g., moving, renovation, travel planning", "📋 Ongoing Tasks — e.g., weekly planning, to-dos, routines", "💻 Software Project — e.g., app, website, automation", "🤔 Not sure yet — set up first, topic comes later"]</options>
+</ask_followup_question>
+
+### Step 3: Create folder structure
+Create the following files based on the user's answer:
+
+**\`.resonance/01_state.md\`**:
+\`\`\`markdown
+# Current State
+
+## Last Sync
+**Date**: [today's date]
+**Session**: Initial setup
+
+---
+
+## Work Package 1: [Name based on user's answer]
+
+### Phase
+Kickoff
+
+### Goal
+[Based on what the user described]
+
+### Context
+- Resonance Framework initialized
+- First chat started
+
+### Next Session
+- [First meaningful task based on the project]
+\`\`\`
+
+**\`.resonance/02_memory.md\`**:
+\`\`\`markdown
+# Memory — Lessons Learned
+
+## [today's date] - Resonance Setup
+**Setup**: Framework initialized
+**Project type**: [What the user chose]
+\`\`\`
+
+**\`.resonance/00_soul.md\`** — Only create if the user described a concrete project:
+\`\`\`markdown
+# Soul — Vision & North Star
+
+## Project
+**Name**: [Project name]
+**Goal**: [One sentence]
+**For whom**: [Target audience / users]
+\`\`\`
+
+**\`docs/\`** — Create the directory. Tell the user that finished documents will be stored here.
+
+### Step 4: Confirmation
+Confirm to the user:
+"Done! 🎉 Your Resonance memory system is set up:
+- 📄 **\`.resonance/01_state.md\`** — This always shows what we're currently working on
+- 🧠 **\`.resonance/02_memory.md\`** — This is where I store important insights
+- 📁 **\`docs/\`** — This is where we store finished documents
+
+From now on, I'll automatically remember our progress. When you open a new chat, I'll know exactly where we left off.
+
+Should I get started with [first task from the work package]?"
+
+## Important rules
+- Keep the setup short and friendly
+- Do NOT create empty template files — only files with real content
+- If the user picks "Not sure yet": Still create the basic structure, but use a generic work package called "First Steps"
+- Do NOT ask about technical details (programming language, framework) unless the user chose "Software Project"
+</explicit_instructions>\n
+`
+
+export const demoToolResponse = () =>
+	`<explicit_instructions type="demo">
+# Resonance Framework — Guided Demo
+
+Walk through a simulated first day with Resonance. Each step demonstrates a core capability: persistent memory, document creation, human-in-the-loop collaboration, AI-assisted editing, live API integration, and session continuity.
+
+**Language Note**: All responses and interactions will automatically adapt to match the language the user is speaking. If the user communicates in German, respond in German. If in English, respond in English. Match the user's language throughout the entire demo.
+
+## ⚠️ CRITICAL PACING RULE — ONE STEP AT A TIME
+
+This is the MOST IMPORTANT rule for this demo:
+
+1. **Complete exactly ONE step per response.** Never combine multiple steps in a single response.
+2. **After completing a step, STOP.** Do not continue to the next step in the same response.
+3. **Every step MUST end with an \`ask_followup_question\`.** This is the only mechanism to pause and wait for the user. If a step doesn't have one, you are doing it wrong.
+4. **Never skip the explanatory text.** Each step has context that helps the user understand what they're seeing — always include it before performing actions.
+5. **Tool calls within a step are fine** (e.g., reading files within Step 2). But do NOT start the next step's tool calls.
+
+Example of WRONG behavior: Reading files (Step 2) + creating invitation (Step 3) in the same response.
+Example of CORRECT behavior: Reading files → give briefing → ask_followup_question → STOP → wait for user → THEN do Step 3.
+
+## Demo Context — Birthday Party Planning
+
+This demo simulates a project that has been running for a few weeks. You will CREATE the .resonance/ files below to set the scene, then give the user a briefing as if these files were already there from previous sessions.
+
+### File: .resonance/01_state.md
+Create this file with the following content:
+\`\`\`markdown
+# Current State
+
+## Last Sync
+**Date**: [calculate: 20 days before today's date, format YYYY-MM-DD]
+**Session**: Party Planning — Location Research & Guest List Draft
+
+## ⚠️ Overdue Items
+- **Invitations** (due [22 days before today], now overdue) — Need to send them this week, party is in 3 weeks!
+
+---
+
+## Work Package 1: Sarah's 30th Birthday Party
+
+### Phase
+Planning & Organization — Date set, location research ongoing, many details still open
+
+### Goal
+Organize an unforgettable 30th birthday party for Sarah on Saturday, [10 weeks from today, pick the nearest Saturday] at 7:00 PM. Budget: ~€1,200 for 25 guests. Italian cuisine (Sarah's favorite), outdoor if possible, relaxed but stylish atmosphere.
+
+### Context
+- **Date confirmed**: Saturday, [same Saturday as above], 7:00 PM
+- **Guest count**: Approximately 25 people (close friends, college crew, work colleagues)
+- **Budget**: €1,200 total (€40-50 per person)
+- **Location research completed**: 3 options identified:
+  1. Osteria Bella Vista — Italian restaurant with garden (outdoor seating, €45/person)
+  2. Rooftop Lounge "Skybar" — Downtown, great view, cocktails (€50/person, indoor only)
+  3. Event space "Alte Fabrik" — Can rent for €300, bring own catering (most flexible)
+- **Catering preferences**: Italian cuisine — antipasti, pasta, tiramisu (Sarah's absolute favorite)
+- **Music**: Playlist with 90s hits + Sarah's favorite indie bands (Spotify playlist started)
+- **Decorations**: Balloons, fairy lights, photo wall with memories (Pinterest board created)
+
+### Next Session
+- Decide on location and book it (deadline: this week!)
+- Finalize guest list and send invitations
+- Order decorations online
+- Contact caterer if we choose event space option
+\`\`\`
+
+### File: .resonance/02_memory.md
+Create this file with the following content:
+\`\`\`markdown
+# Memory — Lessons Learned
+
+## What We Know About Sarah
+
+### Food & Preferences
+- **Favorite cuisine**: Italian — especially pasta and tiramisu
+- **Drinks**: Loves Aperol Spritz and good red wine (Chianti)
+- **Dietary restrictions**: None, but several guests are vegetarian (need veggie options!)
+- **Atmosphere preference**: Relaxed but stylish — not too formal, but nice ambiance
+
+### Location Preferences
+- **Outdoor strongly preferred** — Sarah loves garden/terrace settings
+- **Accessibility**: Location should be reachable by public transport (not everyone has a car)
+- **Parking**: Nice to have, but not essential
+
+### Guest Insights
+- **College friends**: Will travel from Cologne — need to send save-the-date early!
+- **Work colleagues**: Mix of introverts and extroverts — music not too loud, areas for mingling and quiet chat
+- **Family**: Sarah's parents and sister confirmed — they'll help with setup
+
+## Planning Insights
+
+### Budget Learning
+- €40-50 per person is realistic for nice Italian catering
+- Renting event space (€300) + own catering might save money but adds coordination effort
+- Restaurant booking is simpler but less flexible for decorations
+
+### Timeline Insights
+- **Book location ASAP** — Popular places fill up fast in summer!
+- **Invitations should go out 3 weeks before** — We're already late!
+- **Decorations**: Order online now (delivery takes 5-7 days)
+- **Playlist**: Start early, get input from Sarah's sister (she knows all her favorite songs)
+
+## Decisions
+
+### Guest List Size
+- **Decision**: Keep it at ~25 people, not 40+
+- **Reason**: More intimate, better conversations, fits budget
+- **Result**: Focused on closest friends + family
+
+### Date & Time
+- **Decision**: Saturday evening at 7:00 PM
+- **Reason**: Weekend, early summer, evening allows for dinner + after-party
+- **Alternative rejected**: Friday evening (too rushed after work)
+\`\`\`
+
+### File: .resonance/backlog/backlog.md
+Create this file with the following content:
+\`\`\`markdown
+# Backlog — Sarah's 30th Birthday Party
+
